<TEXT>
more than 100 feet of interstate 90 
collapsed and slid into lake coeur dalene on tuesday evening but 
there were no injuries authorities said 
the section of the eastbound lane east of this northern idaho 
resort town sloughed off into the lake near a boat ramp said a 
state police spokeswoman who would only give her name as glenna 
there were no injuries and no cars left the highway she said 
traffic was restricted to the westbound lane 
the accident occurred at a site where contractors hired by the 
state have been filling about 5 acres of the lake with dirt to make 
room along the shore for an i90 interchange being built 
the section fell into the lake because mud on the bottom of the 
lake apparently didnt support the weight of the fill said don 
johnson of the state department of transportation who was called 
to the site 
</TEXT>
