<TEXT>
after six decades as an actress and with 
everything from a tony to an emmy to an obie under her arm 
80yearold jessica tandy could have picked up the actress oscar 
and said it was about time 
instead she wondered aloud why the producers of driving miss 
daisy chose someone whose forte is the stage to play a lead in a 
movie 
i think im very lucky they trusted me with such a wonderful 
part miss tandy told reporters backstage at the los angeles 
music center monday night 
they could have picked someone with more experience she 
said drawing incredulous laughter from the press corps i never 
thought of myself as a movie actress 
and the many honors she has earned over the years didnt blunt 
the thrill of winning hollywoods coveted golden statuette 
it means tiptop its very very important she said im 
walking on air at the moment 
informed that she was the oldest winner of an academy award 
miss tandy replied am i the oldest well good for me but not 
by much in 1976 george burns won for his supporting performance 
in the sunshine boys he was 80 and three months at the time 
miss tandy is 80 and nine months 
she has won many acting honors tony awards for her stage role 
as blanche dubois in a streetcar named desire and her parts in 
the gin game and foxfire an obie for her part samuel 
becketts not i and an emmy for the hallmark hall of fame tv 
production of foxfire 
the actress had fierce competition in the category isabelle 
adjani for camille claudel pauline collins for shirley 
valentine jessica lange for music box and michelle pfeiffer 
for the fabulous baker boys 
miss tandys husband the celebrated actor hume cronyn was 
asked before the 62nd annual academy awards show how it felt to 
have his wife take the spotlight all for herself 
furious jealous unhappy he growled and very proud 
