municipal authorities in the baltic port of swinoujscie the pap 
news agency said 
the official news agency said the refugees first began arriving 
by ferry from sweden on thursday and that at least 300 had been 
denied entry by that country it said polands government has 
appealed to the un high commissioner for refugees in geneva for 
advice on how to deal with the situation 
elzbieta pielamielczarek the mayor of swinoujscie also sent a 
cable to the commissioner appealing for assistance because the city 
does not have the means to provide basic care pap said 
the polish government in the midst of implementing radical 
economic reforms that are seriously taxing the polish people has 
nevertheless decided to grant funds to take care of the refugees 
and has assured them free medical treatment the agency reported 
television showed pictures of the refugees including children 
huddled with their baggage the report also showed refugees in 
swedish buses that were loaded onto a ferry it said some refugees 
were not allowed out of the buses during the 20hour trip across 
the baltic 
here at least is democracy one refugee said in the 
television report most of the refugees hid their faces from the 
television camera however 
we escaped from lebanon because there is war one teenage 
girl said 
the polish government has ordered border officials to check the 
documents of foreigners boarding ferries in the city of swinoujscie 
to see if they have valid entry visas for sweden pap said 
forged swedish visas can be bought in poland on the black market 
from arabs for 200 to 2000 according to the television report 
many of the refugees have run out of money pap said about 300 
of the refugees were being lodged at vacation homes belonging to 
two power plants and another 400 were being housed in private 
homes the agency said 
over the weekend jacek piechota a parliamentary deputy from 
the port of szczecin about 50 miles south of swinoujscie appealed 
to prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki to take action to resolve the 
situation 
