shipment to iran according to a document introduced tuesday at the 
former national security directors irancontra trial 
the document called a stipulation is part of poindexters 
effort to show that he did not try to conceal the us role in the 
missile shipment from congress 
intelligence committee staff members richard giza from the house 
and edward levine from the senate reviewed highly classified 
intelligence information at the national security agency on nov 
20 1986 the document said 
lawyers for poindexter say they will show he approved giza and 
levine going to the nsa and reviewing the data on the reagan 
administrations iran initiative 
the day after the visit poindexter briefed house intelligence 
committee members and the chairman and vice chairman of the senate 
intelligence panel he is accused of obstructing congress and 
making false statements by allegedly telling them he didnt find 
out about the hawk missile shipment until five weeks after it 
occurred 
former nsa legislative liaison kenneth kodama said he watched as 
giza and levine examined a looseleaf notebook containing an inch 
and a half of reports on the iran arms sales 
the reports contained information on the november 1985 delivery 
according to the wording of the stipulation to which both the 
defense and prosecution agreed 
another defense witness former white house computer expert edd 
barnes testified that national security council employees were 
encouraged to delete files from the computer system when they left 
the nsc 
poindexter is accused of deleting 5000 computer files in late 
november 1986 to try to obstruct congress in connection with the 
hawks shipment 
barnes testified that poindexter was very aware of a backup 
tape from which all of poindexters computer messages were 
retrieved the backup tape ordinarily is stripped of old messages 
every two weeks but the tape was preserved in late november 
because of the irancontra affair 
earlier sen john chafee testified as a character witness for 
poindexter 
defense attorney richard beckler asked chafee if he had formed 
an opinion of poindexter for truth and veracity 
he had the highest reputation for truthfulness and 
character chafee said 
poindexter was adminisrative assistant to chafee when the rhode 
island republican was secretary of the navy in the nixon 
administration 
under questioning from irancontra prosecutor dan webb chafee 
said he had had no discussions with poindexter regarding how to 
respond to congressional inquiries into whether oliver north was 
assisting the contras militarily 
poindexter is accused of concealing from congress norths 
military assistance to the contras as well as the us role in the 
november 1985 hawk missile shipment to iran 
