the defense rested its case today in the 
irancontra coverup trial of former national security adviser john 
poindexter after 5 days of testimony 
the case drew to a close without any testimony from poindexter 
who is accused of concealing from congress the us role in a 
november 1985 iran arms shipment and oliver norths secret military 
assistance to the contras 
among the final witnesses for poindexter was rep robert k 
dornan rcalif who testified that there were frequent meetings 
between north and up to 30 congressmen during the period of a 
congressional ban on military aid to the contras 
at the meetings north was told by the congressmen that we 
dont think you are limited by the ban and that it was 
permissible for north to help raise money for the contras dornan 
testified 
since the defense opened its case march 20 poindexters lawyers 
have sought to portray the exnational security adviser as a white 
house official who never lied to congress 
he is accused of conspiracy two counts of obstructing congress 
and two counts of making false statements 
john poindexter is and always has been a person of the highest 
truthfulness honesty and integrity testified retired adm 
james holloway iii a former member of the joint chiefs of staff 
sen john chafee testified earlier in the day that poindexter 
had the highest reputation for truthfulness 
poindexter a retired rear admiral had been administrative 
assistant to chafee when the rhode island republican was secretary 
of the navy in the nixon administration 
meanwhile a document was introduced in court showing that two 
congressional staffers knew about a november 1985 hawk missile 
shipment to iran the day before poindexter allegedly lied about it 
to congress 
the document was a summary of highly classified information 
collected by the national security agency 
defense lawyers plan to show that it was poindexter who 
authorized the release of the information to the staffers that 
would suggest that poindexter had no intent to obstruct congress 
and make false statements when he testified nov 21 1986 because 
