<TEXT>
massachusetts pushed on two fronts tuesday 
to halt the startup of new hampshires seabrook nuclear power 
plant before summer crowds flock to nearby beaches 
state attorneys argued before a nuclear regulatory commission 
appeal board for a temporary shutdown of the plant at the same 
time the lawyers and other seabrook opponents pushed to have 
federal appeals court judges move up the date of a hearing on the 
case from september to this spring 
were trying to get a hearing before summer said john 
traficonte who is handling the case for massachusetts attorney 
general james shannon that is the time of year when thousands of 
people will be sitting on the beaches 
in tuesdays hearing before the atomic safety and licensing 
appeal board traficonte argued that an error made by plant 
operators during lowpower testing in june warranted a second look 
and that the plants operating license should be suspended in the 
meantime 
plant spokesman ron sher called the latest legal manuvers by 
massachusetts just another effort to delay the operation of 
seabrook station for no good reason 
the fact is seabrook is a safe plant sher said 
massachusetts and other opponents have argued for years that 
seabrook was too close to densely populated coastal areas to allow 
for safe evacuation in a nuclear emergency the nrc rejected those 
arguments march 1 and awarded seabrook an operating license 
the plant already has begun to move toward full power a process 
that will take about three months 
traficonte said one of the most dangerous times in the operation 
of any nuclear plant is the first acceleration to full power under 
the current schedule seabrook will be in its first weeks of 
fullpower operation during the summer when tens of thousands of 
beachgoers flock to nearby resort towns 
on june 22 seabrook operators conducting lowpower testing 
didnt shut down the plant after a valve failure when guidelines 
indicated it should have been shut down the nrc ordered a halt to 
testing and fined seabrook 50000 
traficonte said the nrc made its licensing decision in march 
without resolving the problems that led to the june incident 
sher rejected those arguments 
the power ascension program is a very safe conservative 
program sher said more than 100 plants have gone through the 
power ascension program safely in the united states 
sher said that the problems that led to the june incident have 
been corrected 
the appeal board said it wanted more information from shannons 
office and the seabrook operators and gave both parties up to 17 
days to comply 
</TEXT>
