news and entertainment to cuban listeners since 1985 radio marti 
was not jammed tuesday morning nor did cuba interfere with radio or 
television stations in the united states 
the tv marti signal was sent from an antenna aboard a balloon 
dangling 10000 feet above cudjoe key off the south florida coast 
technical problems have delayed testing for months 
the project has had strong support from conservative elements of 
the cuban exile community who believe that televised exposes about 
the demise of communism around the world will weaken castros rule 
once the testing ends the bush administration has three months 
to make a legal and technical evaluation of the operation 
according to the legislation that authorized the station 
ms tutwiler said international agreements do not prevent a 
country from engaging in television broadcasting to another 
country she also noted that the un universal declaration of 
