operation a hospital spokeswoman said tuesday 
cindy martin 26 died monday evening at presbyterianuniversity 
hospital said spokeswoman lisa rossi mrs martins family 
including her husband john were with her when she died 
the resident of the scranton suburb of archbald underwent a 
21hour operation dec 23 in which the heart the liver and the 
kidney were transplanted one after another 
mrs martin contracted recurrent nona nonb hepatitis an 
unusual and noncontagious form of the liver disease which resulted 
in kidney failure doctors said 
her condition was further complicated by an overwhelming 
infection called sepsis a common posttransplant complication ms 
rossi said 
infection is a common problem with transplant patients because 
of the use of antirejection drugs which suppress the immune 
system ms rossi said 
since the surgery mrs martins condition never improved beyond 
serious and she often breathed with the aid of a respirator ms 
rossi said last weekend mrs martins condition deteriorated to 
critical 
mrs martin had suffered from familial cardiomyopathy an 
inherited heart disease her father died at age 31 and many 
relatives on his side of the family have died young her husband 
said in december 
on oct 20 1985 one day after getting married mrs martin was 
admitted to presbyterianuniversity to await her first heart 
transplant she received it a month later 
she subsequently developed hepatitis and kidney dysfunction and 
suffered from chronic rejection of the heart which led to the 
multiple transplant the hospital said 
there had been no sign of rejection of the heart since december 
ms rossi said 
multiorgan transplants have been performed several times but 
this was the first involving all three organs said dr john 
armitage who performed mrs martins heart transplant 
doctors plan to perform similar operations should the need arise 
were not recruiting patients with heart liver and kidney 
problems ms rossi said but i would imagine if someone 
presented themselves again who was in critical need of this 
combination of organs we wouldnt hesitate to give them a second 
chance 
</TEXT>
