<TEXT>
china has accepted indonesian proposals for 
settling outstanding debts removing the last obstacle to restoring 
diplomatic relations suspended 23 years ago the government said 
wednesday 
the official xinhua news agency said the countries concluded 
four days of talks tuesday and agreed that indonesian foreign 
minister ali alatas will visit beijing in late april or early may 
to complete the settlement on indonesias debts to china 
the nations suspended diplomatic relations in 1967 after 
indonesia accused china of complicity in a communist coup attempt 
in 1965 
xinhua did not give a figure for indonesias debt but it quoted 
an unidentified foreign ministry source as saying figures presented 
by the countries were for the most part identical and that china 
accepted an indonesian proposal 
indonesia has said it owes 50 million to china 
the indonesian delegation in the talks that just ended was led 
by jusuf anwar director of external funds of the directorate 
general of budget of the ministry of finance he met monday with 
vice foreign minister qi huaiyuan who welcomed what he said was 
the first official indonesian delegation to visit china since 1967 
agreement to normalize relations came when indonesian president 
suharto and chinese foreign minister qian qichen met in tokyo in 
february 1989 while attending the funeral of japans emperor 
hirohito 
