<TEXT>
columbia university is opening the first public gallery in new 
york devoted exclusively to architecture 
the gallery space in buell hall which was constructed in 1876 
consists of 4100 square feet the building also houses the school 
of architecture 
the first exhibition in the new gallery opens april 4 and runs 
through may 11 the filter of reason work of paul nelson 
focuses on the work of the american architect movie set designer 
painter and critic who taught and practiced architecture in the 
united states and france for more than 50 years 
nelson helped develop functionalism in the 1930s and 40s a 
movement that rejected beauxarts traditionalism 
elsewhere the solomon r guggenheim museum has received an 
unrestricted gift of 5 million from akira tobishima president and 
chief executive officer of tobishima corp an international 
engineering and construction company based in tokyo 
