<TEXT>
for a little over a year in 
188889 vincent van gogh painted with a passionate frenzy 
producing about 200 oils and 100 drawings 
from this creative compulsion emerged some of the most popular 
works of art ever van goghs vibrantly colored sunflowers fishing 
boats and country scenes 
a blockbuster exhibit of his most famous artworks is the 
centerpiece of a fourmonth extravaganza commemorating the 100th 
anniversary of the dutch impressionists death more than 380 van 
gogh paintings and drawings insured for a record 31 billion are 
on display in two dutch museums 
they include self portrait with bandaged ear starry 
night and night cafe as well as dozens of drawings so 
vulnerable to light that they have never been shown in public 
according to the events organizers 
along with the exhibit in amsterdams vincent van gogh museum 
and the kroellermueller museum in the central netherlands town of 
otterlo the commemorative program includes a dozen other art 
exhibitions an opera and a film festival 
commemorative posters by 20 contemporary artists including 
czechoslovak jiri kolar dutchman willem de kooning and american 
roy lichtenstein have been run off to help offset the 115 million 
exhibition cost 
lots of people can relate to van goghs artworks because 
theyre so full of color but his life fascinates people too 
said madeleine wardenaar of the van gogh 1990 foundation which is 
organizing the program hes really the romantic artist with 
drama playing a part in every period of his life 
born on march 30 1853 in the southern netherlands village of 
zundert van gogh struggled with poverty loneliness and periodic 
bouts of madness until he died after firing a rifle into his chest 
on july 29 1890 
during his troubled life van gogh rode an emotional 
rollercoaster after he mutilated himself by removing his ear he 
said the bible had instructed him to cut off the offending 
organ 
one of his closest relationships was with the french painter 
paul gauguin with whom he had an affair they spent endless hours 
arguing 
van gogh also was a voluminous letter writer during that 
444day period in 188889 he wrote about 200 letters 
in a sept 19 1888 letter to his brother theo van gogh 
describes starry night 
the sky is bluegreen the water is royal blue the soil is 
mauve the city is blue and violet the gas light yellow on 
the bluegreen field of the sky the great bear sparkling green and 
pink a reflection whose modest shine contrasts with the powerful 
gold of the gas light two colorful figures of a lovers couple on 
the foreground 
the painting in which the artist departed from his usual method 
of applying small dots of contrasting colors on the cloth to form a 
pattern has bold linear brush strokes 
van gogh enjoyed considerable acclaim among his fellow artists 
during his lifetime but experts disagree whether he sold three 
paintings or just one according to wardenaar 
today his works fetch record prices at art auctions around the 
globe his irises became the most expensive work ever auctioned 
when sothebys sold it for 5390 million on nov 11 1987 the 
painting subsequently was sold to the getty museum in malibu 
calif after australian tycoon alan bond could not repay a loan 
sothebys had posted for the sale 
sunflowers went for 3992 million in march 1987 the 
trinquetalle bridge brought 2024 million in a june 1987 auction 
the van gogh exhibit is expected to attract 15 million visitors 
the amsterdam museum home of the worlds largest van gogh 
collection will display 135 paintings including 80 borrowed from 
museums and private collections in paris london new york boston 
moscow and zurich a total of 248 van gogh drawings and watercolors 
are going on display in the museum in otterlo 62 miles from the 
dutch capital 
despite the theft in otterlo of three van gogh paintings in 
1988 the exhibits organizers had little trouble getting the works 
they wanted from foreign lenders wardenaar said 
the stolen paintings recovered unharmed several months later 
included an early version of van goghs famous the potato 
eaters their total worth was estimated at more than 105 
million 
security during transport and the exhibit itself is expected to 
be extremely tight although no details are being disclosed 
wardenaar said the huge insurance package is costing organizers 
21 million and will cover only the borrowed artworks those owned 
by the dutch museums are uninsured in line with culture ministry 
policy 
the centenary exhibit is organized along the thematic lines that 
van gogh himself described in the hundreds of letters he wrote to 
his brother from france where he lived most of his life 
he said quite explicitly in the letters how he wanted his 
paintings displayed wardenaar said adding the exhibit will 
include some works in several versions in order to illustrate their 
development 
in an april 21 1888 letter to the painter emile bernard van 
gogh wrote from the southern french city of arles 
heres a new orchard fairly simple in composition a white 
tree a small green tree a square bit of green a purple patch of 
soil an orange roof a large blue sky i have nine more orchards 
coming a white a pink an almost red a bluewhite and pink and 
gray a green and a pink one yesterday i botched a cloth a 
cherry tree against a blue sky the sprouting leaves were orange 
and gold the flower clusters white all that against the 
bluegreen of the sky it was simply wonderful 
also part of the centenary extravaganza is an opera by the dutch 
composer jan van vlijmen unhappy man dressed in black which 
focuses on the final years of the artists life 
in the western city of haarlem there will be an exhibit of 75 
works by the 17th century dutch master frans hals whom van gogh 
strongly admired including works on loan from the national gallery 
in washington and the royal academy in london several exhibitions 
in amsterdam and elsewhere will illustrate van goghs effect on 
contemporary artists 
the van gogh anniversary also has attracted mass merchandising 
american express is offering a van gogh bust by dutch artist theo 
melchior it sells for 490 there also are van gogh wines 
aftershave lotion tshirts watches and goldframed prints of his 
paintings for 630 each 
dutch companies sponsoring the van gogh centenary are setting up 
a van gogh village to promote their products on amsterdams 
museum square although wardenaar said everything was being done to 
make the display as dignified as possible 
the centenary exhibit runs through july 29 tickets on sale by 
ticketron in the united states and available in some european 
countries sell for 1250 each and must be ordered in advance 
they will give access to one of the museums at a specific time and 
date although visitors can then stay as long as they want 
</TEXT>
