<TEXT>
atampt has entered the crowded credit card 
business with mastercard and visa cards that promise no annual fees 
and offer a discount on longdistance calls 
the atampt universal card can be used to charge longdistance 
phone calls on the companys telephone network as well as the 
traditional goods and services billed to charge cards 
the phone giant kicked off an advertising blitz during monday 
nights academy awards broadcast to highlight some of the cards 
features including 
no annual fee ever for customers who sign up his year and make 
at least one purchase annually 
rentalcar insurance purchase protection and extended product 
warranties which usually are provided exclusively with gold 
bank credit cards aimed at highincome customers 
a 10 percent discount from the regular creditcard rate on 
phone calls charged to the card 
the card carries an annual interest rate of 89 percentage 
points above the prime rate which currently is 10 percent credit 
card and phone call charges will appear on the same bill 
american telephone amp telegraph co officials said the card would 
be offered to those of its 70 million longdistance phone 
subscribers who pass credit checks 
for customers who choose it the universal card will supplant 
the existing atampt phone card which only can be used to charge 
calls about 40 million phone cards are in circulation 
some industry analysts praised the move by the nations largest 
longdistance phone company 
youve got a company with a very wellknown name and already 
in the wallets of a lot of people trying to expand that wallet 
share into the most profitable segment of financial services 
said mark lynch who follows the banking industry for bear stearns 
amp co 
but spencer nilson publisher of a trade letter on the credit 
card industry said atampt would have a hard time making a profit 
without charging an annual fee 
nilson said he believed the move was motivated more by atampts 
need to hang on to its longdistance customers who increasingly 
are being lured away by mci communications corp and us sprint the 
no 2 and 3 longdistance carriers 
from this perspective nilson called the credit cards a very 
smart move 
in december us sprint began issuing a sprint visa card that 
also acts as a phone charge card the card carries a 25 annual 
fee the company said its motivation was to increase the use of its 
phone network 
mci has said it has no plans to issue credit cards 
atampt will issue its cards through universal bank a subsidiary 
of synovus financial corp a bank holding company based in 
columbus ga total system services inc a credit card service 
company controlled by synovus will process the transactions from 
the cards 
under its agreement with synovus atampt will share profits and 
buy card receivables the money owed from customer charges 
receivables frequently are bundled into securities that are traded 
like bonds on wall street 
atampt also has the right to buy up to 15 million newly issued 
shares of total system services stock the company has 159 million 
shares outstanding 
to run the credit card operation atampt hired scores of credit 
card industry veterans including paul kahn former head of first 
chicago corps card division who will run the new division 
atampt originally considered issuing its own credit card to 
compete with mastercard and visa but backed out after market 
research showed consumers wanted to consolidate their cards rather 
than have another one kahn told reporters at a news conference 
industry analysts said fierce competition in the creditcard 
industry also may have dissuaded atampt from the plan 
sears roebuck and cos discover card was the last separate 
card to break into the industry and the retailer endured several 
years of steep losses before it turned the operation around 
alex w hart president and chief executive officer of 
mastercard international said the atampt card could steal customers 
away from other issuers of mastercard and visa however he said 
the atampt card should expand the overall market share for those 
cards 
