<TEXT>
investor harold simmons won a powerful ally 
tuesday in his contest to unseat the board of lockheed corp 
californias 56 billion public employees retirement system 
which owns 500000 lockheed shares 
the pension fund known as calpers said it would back simmons 
ratherthan lockheed chairman daniel tellep after simmons agreed to 
urge his slate of directors to set up a shareholders committee to 
advise the board calpers advocates such panels as a way to exert 
more control over companies in which it invests 
we met with both mr tellep and mr simmons said kayla 
gillan calpers assistant general counsel mr simmons provided 
us a written commitment that if elected he would recommend to his 
slate the creation of a shareholder advisory committee 
in waging a proxy election campaign to get his slate elected to 
the lockheed board simmons has tried to put tellep on the 
defensive with proposals to give lockheed shareholders more input 
he says that if his faction is put in charge he could manage the 
company so as to increase the price of lockheeds stock which has 
plunged nearly 20 per share in recent months 
lockheed closed up 112 at 37 a share tuesday on the new york 
stock exchange 
tellep who contends simmons has no idea how to run a big 
defense company countered on tuesday with his own attempt to woo 
the big institutional shareholders who hold 60 percent of 
lockheeds stock 
he promised them a seat on the board after lockheeds annual 
meeting thursday when the company will announce whether tellep and 
the other directors have been ousted in simmons proxy battle 
we will work with our institutional shareholders to develop a 
list of potential directors from within or outside their ranks who 
could provide additional perspective to our directors tellep 
said in a statement 
we believe that selection of at least one director from that 
list could provide important input to the future of the company 
calpers holds less than 1 percent of lockheeds stock although 
its influence is greater than the stake might suggest 
for example calpers has persuaded occidental petroleum corp to 
allow calpers officials access to occidental directors twice a 
year occidental agreed to the meetings as a compromise after 
calpers demanded a shareholders advisory committee similar to the 
one promised by simmons 
simmons chief lieutenant j landis martin said in a telephone 
interview that calpers is one of many institutional shareholders 
leaning toward simmons 
we feel a real tidal wave coming martin said were 
feeling very good about our position and im virtually sure there 
