grew 67 percent last year after inflation the slowest level of 
real growth since 1982 and a reflection of the countrys sluggish 
exports central bank officials said tuesday 
tallies by the bank of korea showed the 1989 growth rate was far 
down from 1988s 124 percent and the lowest since the gnp grew 59 
percent in 1982 
south koreas economic boom took off in 1986 resulting in a 
doubledigit gnp growth for three years 129 percent in 1986 13 
percent in 1987 and 124 percent in 1988 
